WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:32.365 --> 00:34.167
{\an8}<i>- Uh, hey, guys, it's me,</i>
<i>Kathy with a K.</i>

00:34.234 --> 00:37.370
{\an8}<i>Uh, today I have a new, uh,</i>
<i>"Leaf Haul."</i>

00:37.437 --> 00:40.407
{\an8}<i>I got this one.</i>
<i>It's--oops, sorry.</i>

00:40.473 --> 00:42.308
{\an8}<i>Ooh.</i>
<i>It's a really cool leaf.</i>

00:42.375 --> 00:44.244
{\an8}<i>It's got some--some crinkles.</i>

00:44.310 --> 00:46.112
{\an8}<i>I don't know if you can--</i>
<i>you can see that</i>

00:46.179 --> 00:49.015
{\an8}<i>but probably my--probably</i>
<i>my current favorite leaf.</i>

00:49.082 --> 00:51.618
{\an8}<i>So this next guy</i>
<i>has a funny story.</i>

00:51.684 --> 00:54.320
{\an8}<i>I picked this leaf up,</i>
<i>and the stem broke off.</i>

00:54.387 --> 00:56.523
{\an8}<i>[laughs and snorts]</i>
<i>Can you believe it?</i>

00:56.589 --> 00:59.626
{\an8}<i>Anyhoot,</i>
<i>then we got this guy.</i>

00:59.692 --> 01:01.795
{\an8}<i>Honestly,</i>
<i>just an all-around solid leaf.</i>

01:01.861 --> 01:03.229
{\an8}<i>No complaints.</i>

01:03.296 --> 01:06.433
{\an8}<i>[light piano music]</i>

01:06.499 --> 01:13.239
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:13.306 --> 01:16.342
{\an8}<i>So if you want to talk leaves,</i>
<i>just "leaf"...</i>

01:16.409 --> 01:18.445
{\an8}<i>[snorts]</i>
<i>A comment below.</i>

01:18.511 --> 01:21.648
{\an8}<i>I'd love to talk with someone,</i>
<i>anyone.</i>

01:21.714 --> 01:23.283
- Incredible.

01:23.349 --> 01:25.985
What other gems of knowledge
does the leaf community hold?

01:26.052 --> 01:27.454
Tell me more.

01:27.520 --> 01:30.190
{\an8}[electronic beep]
No comments?

01:30.256 --> 01:32.792
{\an8}And it's only been viewed
four times?

01:32.859 --> 01:34.861
{\an8}Wait.
It's dropping?

01:34.928 --> 01:36.196
{\an8}How is that even--

01:36.262 --> 01:38.832
{\an8}More people need to see
Kathy's video.

01:38.898 --> 01:39.866
{\an8}[grunting]

01:39.933 --> 01:42.802
{\an8}Dang it.
Every time.

01:42.869 --> 01:44.771
<i>- Got this one.</i>
<i>It's a really cool leaf.</i>

01:44.838 --> 01:45.972
<i>- It's got some crinkles.</i>

01:46.039 --> 01:48.608
{\an1}- [laughs]
She really likes leaves, huh?

01:48.675 --> 01:49.876
- I wish I knew her.

01:49.943 --> 01:51.211
- You do know her.

01:51.277 --> 01:52.946
She hangs out all the time.

01:53.012 --> 01:55.882
both: Uhh...

01:55.949 --> 01:58.351
{\an3}- Looks like you're gonna get
a scar after all.

01:58.418 --> 01:59.919
- You mean it?
- Yup.

01:59.986 --> 02:01.321
Congratulations, dude.

02:01.387 --> 02:03.623
- I'm so happy for you.

02:03.690 --> 02:05.658
- Congratulations, Harvey.

02:05.725 --> 02:08.061
- Be careful, Princess!
I don't want you to--

02:08.127 --> 02:09.496
- Ahh!
[crashing]

02:09.562 --> 02:11.297
- Bye, Princess.

02:11.364 --> 02:13.333
{\an3}- Uh, guys,
this looks dangerous.

02:13.399 --> 02:15.735
{\an3}I'm gonna leave before someone
really gets hurt.

02:15.802 --> 02:18.371
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

02:18.438 --> 02:21.441
- This was a terrible idea!

02:21.508 --> 02:23.376
- Whee!

02:23.443 --> 02:26.045
- Ehh, yeah,
not ringing a bell.

02:26.112 --> 02:28.381
- I have face blindness.

02:28.448 --> 02:29.849
{\an3}[giggles]

02:29.916 --> 02:32.685
{\an1}- We're literally sitting
in her living room right now.

02:32.752 --> 02:35.388
{\an1}- If you want some more cookies,
please help yourselves.

02:35.455 --> 02:37.357
{\an1}- How come you like leaves
so much?

02:37.423 --> 02:39.492
- I don't know;
they're always around,

02:39.559 --> 02:43.630
and nobody notices them,
kind of like me.

02:43.696 --> 02:45.532
[sniffs]
Ahh.

02:45.598 --> 02:47.467
{\an3}- Are those the leaves
for your next video?

02:47.534 --> 02:49.502
{\an3}I'm not looking,
no spoilers.

02:49.569 --> 02:51.838
- You must get tons
of letters from kids

02:51.905 --> 02:53.206
who like leaves too, huh?

02:53.273 --> 02:54.841
- Not really.

02:54.908 --> 02:57.143
Sometimes I feel like the only
one who cares about this stuff.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.311
- People care.

02:58.378 --> 03:00.146
They just don't know they care.

03:00.213 --> 03:02.615
Kris and Trev get people
to care all the time.

03:02.682 --> 03:05.885
- Yeah, but I don't have as big
of an audience as Kris and Trev.

03:05.952 --> 03:07.921
- I'll get Kris and Trev
to share your videos!

03:07.987 --> 03:10.456
Then you'll have tons of people
to talk with.

03:10.523 --> 03:13.359
{\an1}- [whispering]
Who are Kris and Trev?

03:13.426 --> 03:15.728
- I don't know!

03:15.795 --> 03:16.829
{\an8}<i>[upbeat music]</i>

03:16.896 --> 03:18.331
{\an8}<i>both: Hey, everyone.</i>

03:18.398 --> 03:19.933
{\an8}<i>- I'm Kris.</i>
<i>- Whereas I'm Trev.</i>

03:19.999 --> 03:21.334
{\an9}<i>- And today's video</i>
<i>is about shoes.</i>

03:21.401 --> 03:23.002
{\an8}<i>This is my shoe!</i>
<i>- Whoa!</i>

03:23.069 --> 03:24.370
{\an8}<i>- I know, right?</i>

03:24.437 --> 03:26.105
{\an7}<i>- Anyway,</i>
<i>that's all for this week.</i>

03:26.172 --> 03:27.206
{\an7}<i>Click here to watch a video</i>
<i>of us holding a banana</i>

03:27.273 --> 03:28.908
{\an8}<i>over our heads.</i>

03:28.975 --> 03:30.577
{\an8}<i>- Click here to preorder</i>
<i>a book we almost wrote.</i>

03:30.643 --> 03:32.278
{\an7}<i>- Don't forget to send us</i>
<i>a picture of you</i>

03:32.345 --> 03:33.980
{\an7}<i>holding baby clothes</i>
<i>with the rashtag</i>

03:34.047 --> 03:35.682
{\an8}<i>"I used to be a baby."</i>

03:35.748 --> 03:37.750
{\an8}both: Bye!

03:37.817 --> 03:39.152
{\an8}- Okay, uploading video.

03:39.218 --> 03:40.954
{\an9}- We've already got
12,000 likes.

03:41.020 --> 03:42.221
{\an8}- Hey, Kris and Trev!

03:42.288 --> 03:44.023
{\an8}- Hey, you!
- Ugh, get over here.

03:44.090 --> 03:45.725
{\an8}- We love our fans?
- Wha?

03:45.792 --> 03:47.393
{\an8}[camera shutter clicks]

03:47.460 --> 03:50.229
I actually came here
to ask you guys for help.

03:50.296 --> 03:52.732
- Oh, okay, go.
- I've got this friend Kathy.

03:52.799 --> 03:55.335
I want to help her videos
get seen by more people.

03:55.401 --> 03:57.103
<i>- Uh, today I have a new...</i>

03:57.170 --> 03:58.204
{\an3}- O-M-G.
I don't need to see anymore.

03:58.271 --> 03:59.539
She's incredible!

03:59.606 --> 04:00.907
{\an1}- This is the greatest thing
I've ever seen,

04:00.974 --> 04:02.375
and I saw a circus once.

04:02.442 --> 04:05.044
{\an3}- But you've only seen
four seconds--

04:05.111 --> 04:06.212
{\an1}- Okay, her mouth
is so weird and tiny.

04:06.279 --> 04:07.814
{\an1}I'm sorry.
I love it. Ugh!

04:07.880 --> 04:10.383
{\an3}- It's like a robot and a bucket
had a baby underwater.

04:10.450 --> 04:12.919
{\an1}- Okay, we'll take Cat-Pee
under our wing.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.253
- Oh, it's Kathy.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.089
- Totally, Crab Cheese.
- Okay, remind me.

04:16.154 --> 04:17.390
It's Kookoobara?

04:17.457 --> 04:19.791
- It's Kathy.

04:19.858 --> 04:22.695
- Kaa-trrl...

04:22.762 --> 04:24.497
{\an1}I can't do it.
It's impossible. Sorry.

04:24.564 --> 04:26.265
{\an3}- If you can help her find
a few more kids

04:26.332 --> 04:28.635
{\an3}who love leaves
just as much as she does,

04:28.701 --> 04:30.036
that'd be great.

04:30.103 --> 04:32.138
- Oh, with our help,
she has the potential to be

04:32.205 --> 04:33.506
a viral sensation.

04:33.573 --> 04:35.008
{\an1}- Yeah,
she's gonna get more likes

04:35.074 --> 04:37.243
{\an1}than that video
of a kid fighting bees.

04:37.310 --> 04:39.512
<i>- Ahh! Ahh!</i>

04:39.579 --> 04:41.914
- Kathy will be so excited!

04:41.981 --> 04:43.383
{\an8}<i>both: Hey, everyone!</i>

04:43.449 --> 04:45.318
{\an8}<i>- I'm Kris.</i>
<i>- Whereas I'm Trev.</i>

04:45.385 --> 04:48.121
{\an9}<i>- Today we have someone</i>
<i>amazing to show you.</i>

04:48.187 --> 04:49.389
{\an8}<i>- Uh, hey guys.</i>

04:49.455 --> 04:51.591
{\an8}<i>It's me,</i>
<i>Kathy with a K.</i>

04:51.658 --> 04:53.059
{\an7}<i>This is probably</i>
<i>my current favorite leaf.</i>

04:53.126 --> 04:55.128
{\an8}- Amazing!

04:55.194 --> 04:58.264
{\an8}Oh, my...
[mumbling]

04:58.331 --> 05:02.168
{\an8}<i>- Today I have a...</i>
- Ohh, neat!

05:02.235 --> 05:03.636
{\an8}- I want to see!
[all speaking at once]

05:03.703 --> 05:05.505
{\an9}- You guys, I'm trying
to watch a video!

05:05.571 --> 05:07.540
{\an8}Cut it out!
No, I get to--

05:07.607 --> 05:09.208
{\an8}<i>[ding]</i>

05:09.275 --> 05:10.710
{\an8}<i>[dinging]</i>

05:10.777 --> 05:13.446
{\an1}- Wow, Kathy,
you have so many likes!

05:13.513 --> 05:16.315
{\an3}- Ooh.
Oh, this one's orange.

05:16.382 --> 05:18.518
- Do it. Ask her.
- Uh, excuse me.

05:18.584 --> 05:21.487
Are you Leaf Girl?
- Oh, are you talking to me?

05:21.554 --> 05:23.356
- We saw you in that video.

05:23.423 --> 05:26.993
- Oh, um, okay.
Want to look at some leaves?

05:27.060 --> 05:28.728
- Oh, my gosh.
You're famous!

05:28.795 --> 05:31.130
{\an3}- I'm gonna tell everyone
I saw you.

05:31.197 --> 05:32.865
both: Ahh-ahh! Ahh!

05:32.932 --> 05:34.534
- Oh, okay, bye.

05:34.600 --> 05:37.437
Wow, I never get noticed.

05:37.503 --> 05:41.174
It's, uh, pretty
un-be-leaf-able.

05:41.240 --> 05:42.208
[snorts]

05:42.275 --> 05:44.010
- [laughs]
Good one.

05:44.077 --> 05:45.445
{\an3}- Uh-oh.

05:45.511 --> 05:47.313
{\an3}It's the girl taking the world
by storm.

05:47.380 --> 05:48.948
{\an3}- Ooh-ooh!

05:49.015 --> 05:52.585
{\an1}- Okay, girl, your video is
getting so many fan responses.

05:52.652 --> 05:54.854
{\an1}They're even making
tribute videos.

05:54.921 --> 05:56.989
{\an3}I don't want to hype it up,
but it's the best thing ever.

05:57.056 --> 05:58.558
{\an8}<i>- Uh, hey guys.</i>

05:58.624 --> 06:00.193
{\an8}<i>Today I got</i>
<i>a new "Leaf Haul."</i>

06:00.259 --> 06:02.528
{\an8}<i>[distorted] "Leaf Haul."</i>
<i>"Leaf Haul."</i>

06:02.595 --> 06:04.464
<i>[in normal voice]</i>
<i>This one smells like softness.</i>

06:04.530 --> 06:06.165
<i>Le-le-le-le-le-le-leaves.</i>

06:06.232 --> 06:07.400
<i>[squeakily] Leaves.</i>

06:07.467 --> 06:08.901
[in normal voice]
Oh, oh, whoa.

06:08.968 --> 06:10.636
<i>- [gruffly]</i>
<i>I'm gonna show all of you</i>

06:10.703 --> 06:12.405
<i>how to do Leaf Girl cosplay</i>
<i>starting now!</i>

06:12.472 --> 06:14.273
<i>Look at this leaf!</i>
<i>[snorting]</i>

06:14.340 --> 06:17.276
<i>Smells like softness!</i>
<i>Look at it!</i>

06:17.343 --> 06:18.511
<i>[funky music]</i>

06:18.578 --> 06:21.147
<i>- ♪ Shawtay ♪</i>

06:21.214 --> 06:22.982
<i>♪ Baby,</i>
<i>you're my favorite ♪</i>

06:23.049 --> 06:25.017
<i>♪ Ayy-ayy ♪</i>

06:25.084 --> 06:26.786
<i>♪ Leaf Girl ♪</i>

06:26.853 --> 06:30.556
<i>♪ Always on my mind,</i>
<i>like a plastic bag ♪</i>

06:30.623 --> 06:34.961
<i>♪ Oh, oh-oh,</i>
<i>oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-ohh, oh-oh ♪</i>

06:35.027 --> 06:40.099
{\an3}- Well, that's, um,
creative, uh, I guess.

06:40.166 --> 06:41.434
{\an3}- You need to make
a new video.

06:41.501 --> 06:43.436
{\an3}The fans are hungry
for more.

06:43.503 --> 06:45.571
{\an3}- Let's get you in front
of this green screen,

06:45.638 --> 06:49.275
{\an3}get this fan cranking
for some ambience.

06:49.342 --> 06:51.277
{\an1}- Um, but my leaves
are green too,

06:51.344 --> 06:53.479
{\an1}so won't they disappear
in the video?

06:53.546 --> 06:56.115
{\an3}- Clacky, that face
you're making is gold.

06:56.182 --> 06:57.383
{\an3}More wind!

06:57.450 --> 06:58.751
[wind whooshing]

06:58.818 --> 07:00.586
- Augh.

07:00.653 --> 07:02.388
- Hmm.
- Hey, dude.

07:02.455 --> 07:05.158
Kathy looks kind of bummed.

07:05.224 --> 07:07.560
{\an1}- I know,
but she's so popular now.

07:07.627 --> 07:09.462
I thought that's
what she wanted.

07:09.529 --> 07:11.030
- It's not like crowds
are coming out

07:11.097 --> 07:12.999
to talk leaves and junk.

07:13.065 --> 07:14.066
- That's it!

07:14.133 --> 07:15.768
{\an1}What if we had
a leaf convention?

07:15.835 --> 07:19.939
{\an3}- Or what if my legs
were longer?

07:20.006 --> 07:21.541
[birds chirping]

07:21.607 --> 07:24.844
{\an1}- It's a whole convention
just for people who love leaves.

07:24.911 --> 07:26.045
- Oh, wow.

07:26.112 --> 07:27.547
- Trust me.

07:27.613 --> 07:30.950
{\an1}Everyone's here for one reason,
their love of leeee...

07:31.017 --> 07:33.486
eeeeeee-ee-ee-eeee

07:33.553 --> 07:37.490
eeeeeee-ee-ee-eeee

07:37.557 --> 07:40.359
eeeeeee-ee-ee-ohh

07:40.426 --> 07:43.362
eeeeeee-ee-ee-aves?

07:43.429 --> 07:45.464
{\an3}- Um, this feels
kind of weird.

07:45.531 --> 07:47.266
{\an3}How come my face
is everywhere?

07:47.333 --> 07:51.103
{\an1}- [gruffly] Ha, you call that
a convincing Leaf Girl costume?

07:51.170 --> 07:53.573
{\an1}Man, winning
this cosplay contest

07:53.639 --> 07:56.108
{\an1}is gonna be so easy,
right, Ma?

07:57.944 --> 07:59.412
- Give me money.

07:59.478 --> 08:01.347
- Look, there she is!

08:01.414 --> 08:03.316
- Leaf Girl has arrived!

08:03.382 --> 08:04.550
[all cheering]

08:04.617 --> 08:06.619
[camera shutters clicking]
- Ahh!

08:06.686 --> 08:08.487
{\an1}- All right, y'all,
who wants to see Cab Driver

08:08.554 --> 08:10.056
talk about her new "Leaf Haul"?

08:10.122 --> 08:11.290
{\an3}- Really?

08:11.357 --> 08:13.025
all: Leaf Girl! Leaf Girl!

08:13.092 --> 08:15.595
- Um, so this one here
is a fun leaf.

08:15.661 --> 08:17.563
Uh, it's got some bumpies and--

08:17.630 --> 08:20.132
- Now who wants
a photo shoot?

08:20.199 --> 08:22.702
all: Yeah!

08:22.768 --> 08:24.337
{\an1}- Okay, everyone,
grab a leaf,

08:24.403 --> 08:26.072
and pose with it in your photo.

08:26.138 --> 08:27.473
- What?
- Oh, my gosh.

08:27.540 --> 08:30.209
{\an1}I'm such a huge fan
of your videos.

08:30.276 --> 08:32.044
- Oh, when did you
get into leaves?

08:32.111 --> 08:33.746
- Oh, I don't really care
about that.

08:33.813 --> 08:35.448
I just want a picture with you.

08:35.514 --> 08:37.149
- Smile and say "Clam Peas."

08:37.216 --> 08:38.951
[camera shutter clicking]
- Hold still.

08:39.018 --> 08:43.089
I need a leaf
so I can get my picture taken.

08:43.155 --> 08:44.423
<i>[quirky music]</i>

08:44.490 --> 08:45.424
{\an3}- [gasps]

08:45.491 --> 08:46.826
[camera shutter clicks]

08:46.893 --> 08:48.628
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:48.694 --> 08:51.297
No. Uh, uh, uh...
[camera shutters clicking]

08:51.364 --> 08:53.466
all: Leaf Girl!
Leaf Girl!

08:53.532 --> 08:57.069
Leaf Girl! Leaf Girl!
Leaf Girl! Leaf Girl!

08:57.136 --> 08:58.371
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:58.437 --> 09:00.740
{\an3}- Enough!

09:00.806 --> 09:02.208
I--I don't like this.

09:02.275 --> 09:03.910
None of you care about leaves.

09:03.976 --> 09:06.112
I don't want
to make videos anymore.

09:06.178 --> 09:10.116
And my name isn't Leaf Girl.
It's Kathy.

09:10.182 --> 09:12.652
Kathy with a K.

09:12.718 --> 09:14.720
{\an3}- Oh, she seemed
dehydrated.

09:14.787 --> 09:17.323
{\an1}- Guys,
Kathy didn't want fans.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.358
She just wanted some friends.

09:19.425 --> 09:21.227
We really messed things up.

09:21.294 --> 09:23.729
both: Ohh.

09:23.796 --> 09:26.399
Ooh.

09:26.465 --> 09:28.067
[leaf rustling]

09:28.134 --> 09:29.735
- Oh, that's a nice one.

09:29.802 --> 09:33.172
Oh, it's got some sparkles,
a fun shape, right?

09:33.239 --> 09:34.573
Uh, anyone?

09:34.640 --> 09:36.275
Oh, yeah.

09:36.342 --> 09:37.610
Oh.
Oh, hey, little bug.

09:37.677 --> 09:39.245
What do you think?

09:39.312 --> 09:41.047
Pretty cool leaf, huh?

09:41.113 --> 09:42.415
Oh, okay, bye.

09:42.481 --> 09:46.552
{\an1}Guess it's just me,
like always.

09:46.619 --> 09:49.288
- Kathy, it's not just you.
- Wha?

09:49.355 --> 09:51.824
- I'm sorry everything
got so out of control.

09:51.891 --> 09:54.060
{\an1}I want to try
to make it up to you.

09:54.126 --> 09:56.696
{\an3}- Uh, okay.

09:56.762 --> 09:58.898
Harvey, what are you doing?

09:58.965 --> 10:00.766
[wind sighs]

10:00.833 --> 10:02.601
Wh-what's happening?

10:02.668 --> 10:04.737
- ♪ It's so pretty outside ♪

10:04.804 --> 10:07.306
♪ Leaves are falling
two by two ♪

10:07.373 --> 10:08.507
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

10:08.574 --> 10:10.776
♪ Oh, Kathy ♪

10:10.843 --> 10:14.780
{\an1}♪ We want to look
at leaves with you ♪

10:14.847 --> 10:16.615
♪ They're nature's
little hands ♪

10:16.682 --> 10:20.386
♪ And they're giving you
a standing O-oh-oh ♪

10:20.453 --> 10:22.755
- ♪ Some of them are shiny ♪

10:22.822 --> 10:25.858
- ♪ And some of them
can look like toe-oh-ohs ♪

10:25.925 --> 10:29.929
both: ♪ Though you never really
know-oo-oh-oo-oh, yeah ♪

10:29.996 --> 10:31.931
- ♪ Oh, Kathy ♪

10:31.998 --> 10:35.067
{\an1}♪ We want to look
at leaves with you ♪

10:35.134 --> 10:37.937
♪ Oh, oh, Kathy ♪

10:38.004 --> 10:42.041
{\an1}♪ We want to look
at leaves with you ♪

10:42.108 --> 10:44.210
- This is...wow.

10:44.276 --> 10:46.545
{\an3}- We spent all day collecting
our favorite leaves

10:46.612 --> 10:48.147
{\an3}so you can talk about them
together!

10:48.214 --> 10:51.784
- Harvey, you've--
you've "leafed" me speechless.

10:51.851 --> 10:53.185
- Girl, was that a pun?

10:53.252 --> 10:55.021
- You're bad, Kathy.

10:55.087 --> 10:57.156
[all laughing]

10:57.223 --> 11:00.393
- Guys, where am I?

11:00.459 --> 11:01.427
[rustling]

11:01.494 --> 11:02.828
- Uh, hey guys.
All right.

11:02.895 --> 11:05.064
So I found a lot of leaves
this morning.

11:05.131 --> 11:07.199
Like this one.
It's kind of sticky.

11:07.266 --> 11:08.567
See?

11:08.634 --> 11:10.102
- Ooh!

11:10.169 --> 11:12.371
- Amazing!
- Cool!

11:12.438 --> 11:15.174
<i>[all speaking at once]</i>

11:16.809 --> 11:18.611
- Ahh! No.
[laughs]

11:18.677 --> 11:20.846
{\an3}- Waah!

11:20.913 --> 11:22.281
Ahh!

11:22.348 --> 11:24.216
- Heh-heh-heh-heh-heh.

11:24.283 --> 11:26.252
[all laughing]

11:26.318 --> 11:28.587
[both grunting]

11:28.654 --> 11:30.222
- Smell.
- Ahh!

11:30.289 --> 11:31.624
[mumbling]

11:31.690 --> 11:33.726
[gasping]

11:33.793 --> 11:35.828
[coughing]

11:35.895 --> 11:38.564
{\an1}Wow, Foo, your pants
really are gross.

11:38.631 --> 11:39.865
{\an3}- Told you.

11:39.932 --> 11:41.934
{\an3}He's never washed
'em once.

11:42.001 --> 11:43.469
{\an7}- Oh. Huh?

11:43.536 --> 11:44.570
{\an8}I don't play tennis.

11:44.637 --> 11:45.571
{\an8}- [barking]

11:45.638 --> 11:47.139
{\an8}- Oh, hello.

11:47.206 --> 11:48.340
{\an8}Is this yours?

11:48.407 --> 11:49.708
Here you go.

11:49.775 --> 11:51.143
- [growls]
- Whoa.

11:51.210 --> 11:52.178
- [growling]

11:52.244 --> 11:54.080
- You are so cute.

11:54.146 --> 11:55.347
- [growling]

11:55.414 --> 11:56.882
- [whispers]
I love you.

11:56.949 --> 11:59.485
{\an1}- Ooh, I'm sorry,
little girl.

11:59.552 --> 12:02.254
{\an1}Is Commander Pickles
bothering you?

12:02.321 --> 12:04.690
{\an3}- His name is
Commander Pickles?

12:04.757 --> 12:06.158
That's so adorable!

12:06.225 --> 12:10.629
{\an1}- He is my greatest ally
in this battle we call life.

12:10.696 --> 12:12.298
- Really?
- [laughing]

12:12.364 --> 12:15.668
- Aww, that kid's got
a little friend too.

12:15.734 --> 12:18.170
- Thank you for your
unconditional love.

12:18.237 --> 12:19.805
- Pets are so great.

12:19.872 --> 12:21.440
Don't you guys
wish you had one?

12:21.507 --> 12:24.743
{\an1}- I just laid on an anthill,
so I'm covered in pets!

12:24.810 --> 12:26.312
- Foo's kind of like my pet.

12:26.378 --> 12:28.314
- I love my life!

12:28.380 --> 12:29.315
[laughs]

12:29.381 --> 12:31.817
{\an1}- Aww,
I want one so bad.

12:31.884 --> 12:33.219
- Let's just take that kid's.

12:33.285 --> 12:34.220
{\an1}- Fee, no.

12:34.286 --> 12:36.021
I'll get my own pet.

12:36.088 --> 12:38.190
{\an3}- All right,
whatever you want.

12:38.257 --> 12:40.292
- Whee!

12:40.359 --> 12:43.295
<i>[upbeat wacky music]</i>

12:43.362 --> 12:51.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:51.137 --> 12:52.771
{\an1}- Hello, and thank you
for making time

12:52.838 --> 12:55.141
to attend my presentation.

12:55.207 --> 12:57.042
Now, I know
you're a little tired

12:57.109 --> 12:58.544
from dealing with the new baby.

12:58.611 --> 13:02.982
{\an1}So I took the liberty of pouring
you some fresh coffee.

13:05.317 --> 13:07.186
{\an3}- Oww.

13:07.253 --> 13:12.725
- Ahem, today I am here to talk
to you about...pets.

13:12.791 --> 13:14.660
Who needs 'em?

13:14.727 --> 13:16.662
{\an3}Answer: me.

13:16.729 --> 13:19.031
{\an3}There are many great reasons
to own a pet.

13:19.098 --> 13:21.033
{\an3}They're cute.
Some are fuzzy.

13:21.100 --> 13:22.968
As far as I know,
no one's allergic.

13:23.035 --> 13:24.370
[dish shattering]
- Baby!

13:24.436 --> 13:26.172
- Where's the baby?
- Irving, look!

13:26.238 --> 13:29.241
- Michelle, no,
don't you do it.

13:29.308 --> 13:33.279
{\an3}- Heh, I can tell you're busy,
so I'll make this quick.

13:33.345 --> 13:34.647
Home security.

13:34.713 --> 13:36.849
You can never be too safe.
[dishes clattering]

13:36.916 --> 13:38.484
- She's over there!
- Hurry!

13:38.551 --> 13:39.852
- Uh...love.

13:39.919 --> 13:41.820
{\an3}I love pets,
and love is important.

13:41.887 --> 13:44.356
- Catch her!
- How is she so fast?

13:44.423 --> 13:46.158
- Oof!
[groaning]

13:46.225 --> 13:48.494
{\an3}- Also, pets don't cost
a lot of money.

13:48.561 --> 13:49.995
- She's behind you!

13:50.062 --> 13:52.364
- [panting]
Gotcha!

13:52.431 --> 13:55.534
- And that concludes
my presentation.

13:55.601 --> 13:57.570
So what do you guys think?

13:57.636 --> 13:59.205
{\an1}- Son, we loved
the presentation.

13:59.271 --> 14:01.407
{\an1}The animated transitions
were fantastic.

14:01.473 --> 14:03.042
{\an1}But, uh...

14:03.108 --> 14:05.477
{\an3}- But we have enough critters
to care for right now, sweetie.

14:05.544 --> 14:08.747
- But since it'll be my pet,
I'll care for it.

14:08.814 --> 14:10.749
- Harvey, it's just, uh...

14:10.816 --> 14:12.885
{\an1}a pet is a lot
of responsibility.

14:12.952 --> 14:15.321
{\an1}- Look, I'm gonna show you
I can be responsible.

14:15.387 --> 14:18.490
I'm gonna blow your minds
with how responsible I am.

14:18.557 --> 14:20.526
Responsibility!

14:20.593 --> 14:22.795
[panting]
[door bangs]

14:22.861 --> 14:25.164
{\an3}- We're not having
any more kids.

14:25.231 --> 14:27.099
[knocks]

14:27.166 --> 14:29.501
- Oh, hello, children.

14:29.568 --> 14:31.570
I have been expecting you,

14:31.637 --> 14:35.307
and I know why you are here.

14:35.374 --> 14:36.408
all: Whoa!

14:36.475 --> 14:37.409
- You do?

14:37.476 --> 14:38.844
- Oh, yes.

14:38.911 --> 14:41.447
I can see all things.

14:41.513 --> 14:43.882
You are here to...

14:43.949 --> 14:46.285
chill with my daughter,
Piri Piri.

14:46.352 --> 14:48.120
- Well, no.

14:48.187 --> 14:50.689
I wanted to see if I could have
one of your plants.

14:50.756 --> 14:53.092
{\an3}- Mm-hmm, yes,
you want a plant

14:53.158 --> 14:56.395
so that you can--
so you can, uh...

14:56.462 --> 14:59.498
- Show my parents that I can
care for a living thing?

14:59.565 --> 15:01.000
{\an3}- So that you can show your
parents that you can care

15:01.066 --> 15:02.101
{\an3}for a living thing;
I knew it.

15:02.167 --> 15:03.702
- Wow!
- She's a witch.

15:03.769 --> 15:06.005
- How'd she do that?
You're amazing, Hanzi!

15:06.071 --> 15:08.941
So can we visit
your greenhouse?

15:09.008 --> 15:12.044
- Welcome to my garden
of earthly delights!

15:12.111 --> 15:13.379
- Wow!
- Whoa!

15:13.445 --> 15:17.016
{\an1}- Cool, so you're, like,
adopting a plant?

15:17.082 --> 15:19.184
{\an3}- Yeah, I think I'm ready
to be responsible

15:19.251 --> 15:21.920
{\an3}for the well-being
of another living thing.

15:21.987 --> 15:23.289
- Excuse me.

15:23.355 --> 15:24.790
{\an8}You're standing on my lilies.

15:24.857 --> 15:25.891
{\an8}- Whoops, heh.

15:25.958 --> 15:28.027
{\an1}- So which one
are you gonna get?

15:28.093 --> 15:29.328
- Let's see.

15:29.395 --> 15:32.398
Am I a daffodil
or a lilac kind of guy?

15:32.464 --> 15:34.233
- I think you're
a big ol' pansy.

15:34.300 --> 15:35.434
- Hey!

15:35.501 --> 15:36.969
- What do you think?

15:37.036 --> 15:38.003
- Get this one, Harvey.

15:38.070 --> 15:39.305
[plant chomps]
Ahh-ahh!

15:39.371 --> 15:42.641
- Nah, I need one that's more...
[gasps]

15:42.708 --> 15:44.977
{\an1}This one!

15:45.044 --> 15:46.812
I feel like this guy needs me.

15:46.879 --> 15:48.213
I'll name him Spot!

15:48.280 --> 15:49.748
{\an1}- Because of the spots
on his leaves?

15:49.815 --> 15:52.985
- Because he's forever
got a spot in my heart.

15:53.052 --> 15:54.853
{\an3}- Heh-heh.

15:54.920 --> 15:56.555
<i>- So to reiterate,</i>

15:56.622 --> 15:59.491
<i>you need water,</i>
<i>sunlight from ol' Mr. Sun,</i>

15:59.558 --> 16:01.093
<i>and rich soil.</i>

16:01.160 --> 16:04.029
<i>In fact,</i>
<i>I recommend Johnny's Dirt.</i>

16:04.096 --> 16:05.631
<i>It's the dirt I like.</i>

16:05.698 --> 16:07.466
<i>It's the dirt I trust.</i>

16:07.533 --> 16:10.102
- Dirt?
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

16:10.169 --> 16:13.205
I think you deserve
something better than just dirt.

16:13.272 --> 16:15.174
Don't worry.
I got this.

16:15.240 --> 16:17.209
♪ Soup-soup,
soupy, soupy, soupy, soupy ♪

16:17.276 --> 16:19.845
♪ Soup-soup, soupy,
soupy, soupy, soupy ♪

16:19.912 --> 16:22.915
{\an1}Here you go, buddy,
some star noodle soup.

16:22.981 --> 16:24.850
This stuff is super yummy.

16:24.917 --> 16:27.586
[sizzling and squishing]

16:27.653 --> 16:29.455
{\an3}Okay, Spot.

16:29.521 --> 16:32.491
{\an3}Now it's your job to protect
the house from bad guys.

16:32.558 --> 16:35.027
{\an1}- Hey, Harvey,
I was wonderin' if you...

16:35.094 --> 16:36.929
"Beware of plant"?

16:36.995 --> 16:38.664
{\an1}Easy.
I don't want any trouble.

16:38.731 --> 16:40.032
{\an1}Ahh!

16:40.099 --> 16:41.767
{\an3}- Yay!
You did it!

16:41.834 --> 16:43.102
Who's a good boy?

16:43.168 --> 16:45.371
Who's a good boy?

16:45.437 --> 16:48.107
{\an1}So I like using
my mom's shampoo.

16:48.173 --> 16:50.376
{\an1}It helps protect
against split ends.

16:50.442 --> 16:53.545
[splatting,
leaves rustling]

16:53.612 --> 16:55.080
<i>[quirky music]</i>

16:55.147 --> 16:56.982
Hee-hee-hee, hee-hee.

16:57.049 --> 16:59.151
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:59.218 --> 17:02.321
{\an1}Spot!
Drinking from the toilet?

17:02.388 --> 17:05.290
{\an1}You should know better
than that.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:06.992 --> 17:09.994
Phew.
You had a busy day, huh, buddy?

17:10.061 --> 17:11.896
I think you should take a nap.

17:11.964 --> 17:13.965
Sweet dreams, Spot.

17:14.031 --> 17:15.901
I love you.

17:15.968 --> 17:17.636
[leaves rustling]

17:20.772 --> 17:22.273
- Hey, guys, check it out.

17:22.340 --> 17:24.777
{\an3}I just coughed up a hairball
in the corner over there.

17:24.843 --> 17:26.078
Anyways,
I'm bored now.

17:26.145 --> 17:27.512
Hey, where's Spot?

17:27.579 --> 17:30.182
- Oh, he's taking a nap
in the closet.

17:30.249 --> 17:32.384
- Plants take naps?
I didn't know that.

17:32.451 --> 17:35.454
- Spot's really more of a pet
than a plant.

17:35.521 --> 17:37.723
Check out this drawing
Spot made me.

17:37.790 --> 17:39.158
"Who's walking who?"

17:39.224 --> 17:42.227
{\an3}- Wow, Spot drew this
all by himself?

17:42.294 --> 17:44.263
{\an1}- Well,
he had some help.

17:44.329 --> 17:45.497
- You're the best, Harvey.

17:45.564 --> 17:47.166
{\an3}You're totally gonna get
that pet.

17:47.232 --> 17:48.767
I know.
I'm the best.

17:48.834 --> 17:50.169
- You're totally the best.

17:50.235 --> 17:52.704
- And Spot is totally dead.
- Huh?

17:52.771 --> 17:54.773
{\an1}- See?
Look at him.

17:54.840 --> 17:56.642
<i>[sad piano music]</i>

17:56.708 --> 17:57.810
- Spot!

17:57.876 --> 17:59.478
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

17:59.545 --> 18:02.080
{\an3}You're okay. You're okay.
You're okay.

18:02.147 --> 18:04.550
{\an3}Don't you dare leave me, Spot,
not now!

18:04.616 --> 18:05.751
- Uh...

18:05.818 --> 18:07.786
{\an3}- Come on!
Live, dang it!

18:07.853 --> 18:10.823
{\an3}[sobbing]
He's dead!

18:10.889 --> 18:13.025
I killed him!

18:13.091 --> 18:14.493
[crying]

18:14.560 --> 18:17.362
- Oh, man, you're crying,
like, really hard.

18:17.429 --> 18:20.732
{\an3}- I gave him everything,
and it wasn't enough!

18:20.799 --> 18:24.136
{\an1}- I can tell you...
just need some time alone.

18:24.203 --> 18:26.205
- And I tried...

18:26.271 --> 18:28.240
- Sorry, dude.
We got to go.

18:28.307 --> 18:30.943
I get violent around crybabies.

18:31.009 --> 18:33.812
- Sorry you're a murderer,
Harvey.

18:33.879 --> 18:35.314
- [sobbing]

18:35.380 --> 18:36.615
[gasps]

18:36.682 --> 18:38.317
My parents can't find out
about this.

18:38.383 --> 18:41.420
They'll never trust me
with a real pet if they see you.

18:43.522 --> 18:46.525
{\an1}<i>- Look out, folks.</i>
<i>This guy's a real killer!</i>

18:46.592 --> 18:49.261
{\an1}<i>- You've absolutely murdered</i>
<i>this dress.</i>

18:49.328 --> 18:50.762
<i>- They're dead!</i>

18:50.829 --> 18:52.931
<i>These batteries are dead!</i>

18:52.998 --> 18:54.867
- [gulps]

18:54.933 --> 18:57.870
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

18:57.936 --> 18:59.071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:59.137 --> 19:00.739
[door clicks]

19:00.806 --> 19:02.140
- Harvey, is that you?

19:02.207 --> 19:03.408
- Nothing!

19:03.475 --> 19:06.712
I mean, uh,
what are you up to?

19:08.747 --> 19:10.048
{\an3}- Huh?

19:10.115 --> 19:13.085
{\an8}- Heh, I'm fine.
Everything's fine.

19:13.151 --> 19:15.921
{\an8}Spot is fine.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.556
{\an8}Where is he,
you ask?

19:17.623 --> 19:21.226
{\an8}Uh, well, he went to the store,
library, park, and,

19:21.293 --> 19:23.295
{\an8}uh, movie theater
for a double feature,

19:23.362 --> 19:25.531
{\an8}but he'll be back real soon.

19:25.597 --> 19:28.233
{\an8}Hey, look!
Uh...uh, a babysitter!

19:28.300 --> 19:30.168
both: What? Where?
How much was it?

19:30.235 --> 19:32.437
- [murmurs and yawns]

19:32.504 --> 19:33.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:33.639 --> 19:36.642
- [screaming]
both: Ahh!

19:36.708 --> 19:39.645
<i>[sad piano music]</i>

19:39.711 --> 19:42.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:42.080 --> 19:43.782
- It's cold.

19:43.849 --> 19:47.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:47.419 --> 19:49.454
I'm sorry I failed you, Spot.

19:49.521 --> 19:54.092
I'll always have your mud
on my hands.

19:54.159 --> 19:56.128
Phew, okay, okay.

19:56.194 --> 19:57.763
{\an1}Got to get my story
straight.

19:57.829 --> 20:00.599
Mom, Dad,
you'll never believe it.

20:00.666 --> 20:03.368
Spot ran...away?

20:03.435 --> 20:04.803
[sighs]

20:04.870 --> 20:06.238
I don't think they'll buy that.
[door creaks]

20:06.305 --> 20:07.372
{\an1}- Harvey,
are you out there?

20:07.439 --> 20:09.474
- Mom!
[shovel clangs]

20:09.541 --> 20:11.810
- Can we speak to you
in the kitchen?

20:11.877 --> 20:13.078
- [gulps]

20:13.145 --> 20:14.680
Sure.

20:14.746 --> 20:16.949
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:17.015 --> 20:18.817
<i>[thinking]</i>
<i>They don't know anything.</i>

20:18.884 --> 20:20.552
<i>Keep it cool, big guy.</i>

20:20.619 --> 20:23.488
- So your father and I
were talking earlier.

20:23.555 --> 20:24.790
<i>- [thinking]</i>
<i>Oh, my gosh.</i>

20:24.856 --> 20:26.491
<i>They see right through me!</i>

20:26.558 --> 20:29.061
- Well, we've noticed how
responsible you've been lately.

20:29.127 --> 20:31.363
{\an3}- And we gave it
a little more thought.

20:31.430 --> 20:33.098
<i>- [thinking] Oh, no.</i>
<i>Here it comes.</i>

20:33.165 --> 20:35.367
- Do you want to tell him?
- Let's both tell him.

20:35.434 --> 20:38.170
both: We're getting you
your own pet!

20:38.236 --> 20:41.373
- I killed Spot!

20:41.440 --> 20:43.241
[wailing]
- What?

20:43.308 --> 20:45.677
Uh...who's Spot?

20:45.744 --> 20:50.415
- Spot's dead,
and I buried him!

20:50.482 --> 20:54.086
{\an3}- Hold the phone.
You buried Spot in the ground?

20:54.152 --> 20:56.888
<i>[sad piano music]</i>

20:56.955 --> 20:59.057
- This is where it happened.

20:59.124 --> 21:01.560
{\an3}I'm sorry.
It's horrible.

21:01.627 --> 21:03.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:03.362 --> 21:04.696
{\an1}- I think you should take
another look

21:04.763 --> 21:05.897
at your crime scene.

21:05.964 --> 21:08.333
{\an3}- No, Mom,
I really don't think so.

21:08.400 --> 21:11.169
{\an1}- Harvey,
don't be a baby.

21:11.236 --> 21:12.371
{\an3}- [gasps]

21:12.437 --> 21:15.974
{\an1}Spot's growing
out of the ground?

21:16.041 --> 21:17.709
{\an3}What?

21:17.776 --> 21:19.911
- Sweetie, the only thing
you're guilty of

21:19.978 --> 21:22.280
is loving that plant too much.

21:22.347 --> 21:25.050
{\an1}- Boy, if I had a nickel
for every plant I killed...

21:25.117 --> 21:26.618
[chuckles]

21:26.685 --> 21:28.320
But the point is,
you get over the little stuff,

21:28.387 --> 21:30.122
like dead plants,
and eventually,

21:30.188 --> 21:32.024
you get the big things
figured out too.

21:32.090 --> 21:33.425
[whistling and creaking]

21:33.492 --> 21:35.227
- [giggling]
- What was that?

21:35.293 --> 21:36.561
- You know what, guys?

21:36.628 --> 21:38.030
{\an3}I think I might want
to wait a little longer

21:38.096 --> 21:39.064
before I get a pet.

21:39.131 --> 21:40.599
- Are you sure, son?

21:40.666 --> 21:43.168
{\an3}- Yeah, I think I'll stick
with Spot for a while.

21:43.235 --> 21:46.872
He's about all I can handle.

21:46.938 --> 21:48.707
{\an1}♪ Soup-soup,
soupy, soupy, soupy, soupy ♪

21:48.774 --> 21:50.075
- Harvey, no.

21:50.142 --> 21:51.576
- Oh, right.

21:51.643 --> 21:54.613
{\an1}I forgot.

21:54.680 --> 21:55.981
Mwah!

21:56.048 --> 21:58.850
<i>[bright music]</i>
